cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.DL, cs.DC

The paper discusses the development of a test collection for Content-based Image Retrieval (CBIR) and the use of distributed similarity searching technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves the use of MPEG-7 features for image retrieval, which falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the European EGEE computer GRID for image crawling and feature extraction, which could fall under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability and effectiveness of CBIR approaches, which could also fall under Deep Learning (cs.DL).
